  '3776c230-fae7-479a-8c52-1838f7b3dd4c',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Phoenix Routing — Scopes, Parameters, and Pipeline Grouping$escape$,
  $escape$Phoenix's router lives in `router.ex` and uses a declarative DSL built on `Plug.Router`. Every route is tied to a pipeline — a composable chain of plugs that pre-process requests.

Define basic routes with `get`, `post`, `put`, `delete`, or `resources` for RESTful CRUD. Route parameters use the `:param` syntax and land in `conn.params`:

```elixir
get "/users/:id", UserController, :show
```

Group related routes under a `scope` to share a path prefix and optionally an alias:

```elixir
scope "/api/v1", MyAppWeb do
  pipe_through :api
  resources "/users", UserController, only: [:index, :show, :create]
  get "/users/:id/posts", PostController, :user_posts
end
```

`pipe_through :api` applies the `:api` pipeline (typically JSON parsing, auth plugs). Nest scopes for versioning — an outer `/api` scope with inner `/v1` and `/v2` children. Use `resources` with `:only` or `:except` to avoid generating unused routes. Run `mix phx.routes` to inspect every registered path, verb, and controller action in one shot.$escape$,
  $escape$# router.ex
pipeline :api do
  plug :accepts, ["json"]
  plug MyAppWeb.Auth.VerifyToken
end

scope "/api", MyAppWeb do
  scope "/v1" do
    pipe_through :api

    resources "/users", UserController, only: [:index, :show, :create, :delete]
    get "/users/:id/feed", FeedController, :user_feed
    post "/users/:id/follow", FollowController, :create
  end
end$escape$,
  $escape$elixir$escape$,
